      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) in impeccable condition. This chassis retains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution and remains structurally pristine. Under the hood, the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine delivers seamless power delivery, with recent compression tests confirming exceptional health across all rotor faces. The drivetrain features the original 5-speed short-throw manual gearbox paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential for precise torque management. Suspension geometry is factory-spec with zero bushing deflection, ensuring the double-wishbone setup provides maximum mechanical grip. The exterior features original paint with no swirling, while the cockpit remains a time capsule, free of the common plastic fatigue or bolster wear found in lesser examples. A purist\u2019s dream with no modifications to the vacuum system or ECU.",
